Great news — on .NET 10 SDK, **you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property is only required on .NET 9 and earlier to bridge `dotnet test` with MTP.

**.NET 10 has native MTP support.** Instead, add a `"test"` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": { "version": "10.0.100" },
  "test": { "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform" }
}
```

And **remove** `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from your `.csproj`.

